Decorates a class as an Angular module, providing metadata for the module.

Encapsulation refers to the bundling of data and the methods that operate on the data into a single unit known as a class.
It helps in restricting access to some of the object's components and preventing unintended interference.

Inheritance allows a class to inherit the properties and methods of super class.
It promotes code reuse and establishes a hierarchy of classes.

Polymorphism allows objects of different classes to be treated as objects of a common base class.
It enables a single interface to represent different types of objects.

Abstraction involves hiding the complex reality while exposing only the necessary parts.
Abstract classes and interfaces are used to achieve abstraction.

• Arrow functions: 
	Provide a concise syntax for writing anonymous functions and improve readability.
• Classes: 
	Introduce a more class-like syntax for object-oriented programming, including constructors, methods, and inheritance.
• Modules: 
	Facilitate code organization and modularity with import and export statements.
• Let and const: 
	Offer block-scoped variable declarations instead of the globally scoped var, improving variable management.
• Template literals: 
	Enable string interpolation using backticks (``) for embedding variables and expressions within strings.
• Destructuring: 
	Allow concise extraction of values from arrays and objects into variables.
• Spread operator (...) and rest operator (...) 
	Provide flexible ways to work with arrays and function arguments.
• Promises: 
	Simplify asynchronous programming with a more structured approach to handling eventual completion or failure.
• Default parameters: 
	Allow setting default values for function parameters, enhancing flexibility.

Firstly the Angular CLI recognizes the ng s command.
The CLI searches for the angular.json file for getting the project configuration of Angular CLI
Within angular.json, the CLI looks for the main.js file and index.html file
And inside main.ts bootstraping the application is done ( by using platformBrowserDynamic function) thus loading the AppModule, which is the root module of the application.
AppModule registers components, directives, services, and other building blocks used in the application
and thus the server runs on port 4200 by default
and it also watch for any changes in source file and reload the application

explanation.explanation:
Given a signed 32-bit integer x, return x with its digits reversed. If reversing x causes the value to go outside the signed 32-bit integer range [-231, 231 - 1], then return 0. 
 	Example 1: 	Input: x = 123 
 			Output: 321 
 	Example 2: 	Input: x = -123 
 		   	Output: -321
